for duty,

583
00:25:22,420 --> 00:25:23,260
I'll grab one,

584
00:25:23,660 --> 00:25:24,860
and share it with my daughter.

585
00:25:25,400 --> 00:25:26,500
Walking down the street,

586
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:27,580
she takes a bite,

587
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:28,780
then I take a bite.

588
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:30,777
Then she takes another bite...

589
00:25:36,940 --> 00:25:38,466
Are you missing home?

590
00:25:47,900 --> 00:25:48,980
Longing for home,

591
00:25:50,420 --> 00:25:51,600
in Chang'an.

592
00:25:56,380 --> 00:25:57,220
Cityman,

593
00:25:57,540 --> 00:25:58,380
don't be so down.

594
00:25:58,700 --> 00:26:00,300
It's lively here.

595
00:26:00,820 --> 00:26:02,500
Stay the night with us.

596
00:26:02,980 --> 00:26:03,780
Enjoy a good meal.

597
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:04,740
There's wine too.

598
00:26:06,660 --> 00:26:07,540
We have wine!

599
00:26:17,380 --> 00:26:18,220
Try some.

600
00:26:19,460 --> 00:26:20,300
What's this?

601
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:21,460
Game meat.

602
00:26:22,820 --> 00:26:23,660
Wait...

603
00:26:23,755 --> 00:26:24,700
Is this even edible?

604
00:26:24,820 --> 00:26:25,780
It's delicious.

605
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:33,700
I'll... I'll drink the wine.

606
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:36,420
What, you don't like it?

607
00:26:36,580 --> 00:26:37,140
No.

608
00:26:37,140 --> 00:26:37,980
I'm just thirsty.

609
00:26:44,220 --> 00:26:45,100
What's that flavor?

610
00:26:45,820 --> 00:26:46,660
Rice wine.

611
00:26:46,820 --> 00:26:48,060
Soaked with a few litchis.

612
00:26:48,820 --> 00:26:49,540
I thought so.

613
00:26:49,660 --> 00:26:50,900
I knew March Red just came in.

614
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:52,755
There's no way it's been brewed already.

615
00:26:52,860 --> 00:26:53,940
Why so picky?

616
00:26:54,177 --> 00:26:55,688
As long as it's wine, it's fine.

617
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:57,580
Right.

618
00:26:57,780 --> 00:26:59,220
You seem like a decent guy.

619
00:26:59,622 --> 00:27:01,422
I wouldn't offer this to just anyone.

620
00:27:01,940 --> 00:27:02,780
Drink up.

621
00:27:04,820 --> 00:27:05,660
What's your name?

622
00:27:07,780 --> 00:27:09,140
I'm Li Shande.

623
00:27:09,266 --> 00:27:10,533
Courtesy name Liangyuan.

624
00:27:10,577 --> 00:27:12,620
Li Shande, courtesy name Liangyuan.

625
00:27:13,380 --> 00:27:14,600
Six characters? That long?

626
00:27:15,288 --> 00:27:16,111
Doesn't matter.

627
00:27:16,133 --> 00:27:17,622
Just call me Li Shande.

628
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:19,300
Li Shande.

629
00:27:21,660 --> 00:27:23,300
You said you miss home.

630
00:27:23,820 --> 00:27:25,420
Why haven't you mentioned your wife?

631
00:27:27,020 --> 00:27:27,900
My wife

632
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:30,020
passed away six years ago.

633
00:27:31,740 --> 00:27:33,020
Left me with a little girl.

634
00:27:33,460 --> 00:27:34,500
It's just the two of us.

635
00:27:35,660 --> 00:27:36,500
My daughter

636
00:27:36,660 --> 00:27:37,933
isn't much younger than you.

637
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:40,740
Seems like you're

638
00:27:40,740 --> 00:27:41,860
someone who values love.

639
00:27:42,860 --> 00:27:44,340
I was right about you.

640
00:27:47,620 --> 00:27:49,340
Envoy Li, come dance with us.

641
00:27:49,340 --> 00:27:50,180
No, you go ahead.

642
00:27:50,460 --> 00:27:51,060
You dance.

643
00:27:51,060 --> 00:27:51,900
Come on.

644
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:16,740
Li Shande.

645
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,580
Would you like to stay
in this litchi garden?

646
00:28:19,540 --> 00:28:20,380
I'd love to.

647
00:28:20,844 --> 00:28:22,466
But I still need to
deliver these litchis

648
00:28:22,860 --> 00:28:24,140
to Chang'an for His Majesty.

649
00:28:24,460 --> 00:28:25,340
Then it's settled.

650
00:28:25,860 --> 00:28:26,820
You'll stay and help me.

651
00:28:27,180 --> 00:28:28,420
We'll tend the garden together.

652
00:28:28,740 --> 00:28:29,580
Alright.

653
00:28:30,220 --> 00:28:31,060
Back in Chang'an,

654
00:28:31,066 --> 00:28:32,940
I tended nothing
but flowers and plants too.

655
00:28:33,260 --> 00:28:34,100
I can help you

656
00:28:34,460 --> 00:28:35,420
make this litchi garden

657
00:28:35,820 --> 00:28:36,955
even more prosperous.

658
00:28:37,220 --> 00:28:37,740
Really?

659
00:28:37,740 --> 00:28:38,580
Yes!

660
00:28:39,980 --> 00:28:40,820
Great.

661
00:28:41,977 --> 00:28:43,666
Then we should drink nuptial wine.

662
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:44,940
Nuptial wine?

663
00:28:45,700 --> 00:28:46,780
United in heart and effort.

664
00:28:47,140 --> 00:28:48,500
That's a good omen.

665
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:49,340
Come on.

666
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:52,300
I want to drink nuptial wine with him!

667
00:29:09,740 --> 00:29:15,300
Drink!

668
00:29:23,300 --> 00:29:27,700
Drink!

669
00:29:40,460 --> 00:29:43,060
Drink!

670
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:44,700
Wait, Tong.

671
00:29:45,060 --> 00:29:45,860
Are you mad?

672
00:29:45,911 --> 00:29:47,711
(Yan Yazhuang)
You drank nuptial wine with him!

673
00:29:47,980 --> 00:29:48,980
Doesn't that mean

674
00:29:48,980 --> 00:29:50,288
you're agreeing to marry him?

675
00:29:50,380 --> 00:29:51,700
I think he's nice.

676
00:29:52,540 --> 00:29:53,940
Do you even know him?

677
00:29:54,220 --> 00:29:55,740
When choosing a husband,

678
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:57,044
what do women look for?

679
00:29:57,140 --> 00:29:58,220
Looks, talent,

680
00:29:58,460 --> 00:29:59,420
family status and rank.

681
00:29:59,580 --> 00:30:01,420
He doesn't have any of those.

682
00:30:02,340 --> 00:30:03,940
I don't understand everything he says,

683
00:30:04,420 --> 00:30:05,380
but I can feel

684
00:30:05,380 --> 00:30:06,860
that he's a man of talent.

685
00:30:07,660 --> 00:30:09,020
And he knows farming too.

686
00:30:09,540 --> 00:30:10,220
I need someone

687
00:30:10,220 --> 00:30:11,822
to help me take care of this garden.

688
00:30:12,220 --> 00:30:13,780
That's all just an act.

689
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:15,420
You've only known him for a few days.

690
00:30:15,420 --> 00:30:16,740
He's tricking you.

691
00:30:17,620 --> 00:30:18,460
Tong.

692
00:30:18,860 --> 00:30:19,740
Think about it.

693
00:30:19,900 --> 00:30:20,820
Didn't you say

694
00:30:20,977 --> 00:30:23,088
that your litchi garden
has the best land and water?

695
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:24,700
Every cityman who comes here

696
00:30:24,860 --> 00:30:26,288
wants to take it for themselves.

697
00:30:26,330 --> 00:30:28,266
Why is it that you
trust him of all people?

698
00:30:29,540 --> 00:30:30,660
Well, I trusted you too.

699
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:31,780
Aren't you also a cityman?

700
00:30:31,780 --> 00:30:32,620
Yan Yazhuang.

701
00:30:33,700 --> 00:30:35,820
He won't stay in Lingnan.

702
00:30:35,980 --> 00:30:36,580
Don't forget,

703
00:30:36,580 --> 00:30:37,333
he said it himself.

704
00:30:37,380 --> 00:30:38,580
He has a daughter in Chang'an.

705
00:30:38,980 --> 00:30:39,660
He also said

706
00:30:39,780 --> 00:30:41,180
he was under imperial orders

707
00:30:41,380 --> 00:30:42,780
to deliver litchis to Chang'an.

708
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:44,660
That's 2500 km from Lingnan.

709
00:30:44,860 --> 00:30:46,380
The trip alone takes over a month.

710
00:30:46,700 --> 00:30:47,260
His Majesty

711
00:30:47,260 --> 00:30:48,380
wants fresh litchis.

712
00:30:48,444 --> 00:30:49,933
How's he supposed to get them there?

713
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,733
He might not even survive past June.
That's not certain at all.

714
00:30:53,422 --> 00:30:54,580
So you want to get married

715
00:30:54,580 --> 00:30:55,660
and be widowed right after?

716
00:30:58,460 --> 00:30:59,740
All the more reason to help him.

717
00:31:00,460 --> 00:31:01,420
Enough.

718
00:31:01,420 --> 00:31:02,300
You've ruined

719
00:31:02,300 --> 00:31:03,377
our nuptial wine moment.

720
00:31:03,580 --> 00:31:04,420
Tong!

721
00:31:04,580 --> 00:31:05,420
Don't follow me.

722
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:40,060
Careful now.

723
00:31:40,180 --> 00:31:41,020
Got it.

724
00:31:44,540 --> 00:31:45,380
Envoy Li.

725
00:31:48,980 --> 00:31:49,820
Envoy Li.

726
00:31:50,100 --> 00:31:50,940
Why are you here?

727
00:31:52,580 --> 00:31:53,420
Come.

728
00:31:55,900 --> 00:31:56,900
I ran into trouble.

729
00:31:58,180 --> 00:32:00,420
I had a boat that got seized
by Captain Yang

730
00:32:00,820 --> 00:32:01,980
at Gaozhou Port.

731
00:32:03,022 --> 00:32:04,060
When I reached the port,

732
00:32:04,820 --> 00:32:05,740
I opened the hold.

733
00:32:06,420 --> 00:32:07,260
There was nothing

734
00:32:08,180 --> 00:32:09,220
inside the hold.

735
00:32:11,620 --> 00:32:12,820
I was struck like thunder

736
00:32:13,220 --> 00:32:14,340
and burning with panic.

737
00:32:14,660 --> 00:32:15,180
Su,

738
00:32:15,300 --> 00:32:16,940
no need for all the idioms.

739
00:32:17,260 --> 00:32:18,100
Alright.

740
00:32:18,340 --> 00:32:19,020
So,

741
00:32:19,140 --> 00:32:20,466
that's why I came to you.

742
00:32:21,660 --> 00:32:22,500
This?

743
00:32:23,260 --> 00:32:24,260
You already used

744
00:32:25,140 --> 00:32:26,060
the travel pass.

745
00:32:26,180 --> 00:32:26,540
Yes.

746
00:32:26,660 --> 00:32:27,822
Then it's non-refundable.

747
00:32:27,844 --> 00:32:28,340
Exactly.

748
00:32:28,460 --> 00:32:29,740
And the money you gave me

749
00:32:29,860 --> 00:32:31,140
is already safely in the pouch.

750
00:32:31,260 --> 00:32:32,100
It's no longer yours.

751
00:32:33,380 --> 00:32:34,020
No...

752
00:32:34,140 --> 00:32:36,020
You didn't understand.

753
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:37,580
But I do understand.

754
00:32:38,260 --> 00:32:39,100
My money

755
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:40,420
is already with you,

756
00:32:40,620 --> 00:32:41,660
buried and at peace.

757
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:43,500
I'll never let it

758
00:32:43,660 --> 00:32:44,500
rise from the ashes.

759
00:32:45,022 --> 00:32:46,220
Nor return it to the owner.

760
00:32:50,180 --> 00:32:51,980
You and the Inspector's Office

761
00:32:52,420 --> 00:32:54,500
have a lingering connection.

762
00:32:55,220 --> 00:32:56,420
Could you help me out

763
00:32:56,780 --> 00:32:58,180
and seduce Inspector He?

764
00:32:59,820 --> 00:33:00,780
I just want to know

765
00:33:00,940 --> 00:33:02,460
where my benzoin went.

766
00:33:03,860 --> 00:33:04,700
I...

767
00:33:05,380 --> 00:33:06,260
Even I don't have

768
00:33:06,780 --> 00:33:07,820
that kind of connection.

769
00:33:08,340 --> 00:33:09,900
My only tie to the Inspector...

770
00:33:11,180 --> 00:33:13,020
My only tie to him

771
00:33:13,220 --> 00:33:14,820
was through that travel pass.

772
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:16,460
And now that pass

773
00:33:16,700 --> 00:33:17,580
is in your hands.

774
00:33:17,820 --> 00:33:18,820
Then I've got nothing

775
00:33:19,060 --> 00:33:20,180
to do with them anymore.

776
00:33:20,340 --> 00:33:21,620
I really can't help.

777
00:33:23,260 --> 00:33:24,100
You can't help?

778
00:33:24,540 --> 00:33:25,380
So,

779
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:27,540
can you or can't you?

780
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:29,180
I can't...

781
00:33:29,420 --> 00:33:30,340
Can help?

782
00:33:30,620 --> 00:33:31,500
Really can't help.

783
00:33:32,740 --> 00:33:33,580
Why not?

784
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:35,100
I just can't.

785
00:33:37,540 --> 00:33:38,380
What if

786
00:33:39,380 --> 00:33:40,660
I let more of my money

787
00:33:41,020 --> 00:33:42,660
rest in peace with you?

788
00:33:43,100 --> 00:33:45,060
Would you be able to help then?

789
00:33:45,180 --> 00:33:46,020
How much?

790
00:33:49,060 --> 00:33:49,940
You name a price.

791
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:54,820
It... It's not about the money.

792
00:33:54,820 --> 00:33:55,660
It's just...

793
00:33:56,500 --> 00:33:57,780
I'd really

794
00:33:58,100 --> 00:33:59,220
love to earn money from you.

795
00:34:00,020 --> 00:34:01,380
But I can't.

796
00:34:01,900 --> 00:34:02,740
Why not?

797
00:34:03,460 --> 00:34:04,220
It's just

798
00:34:04,340 --> 00:34:05,220
hard to explain.

799
00:34:05,660 --> 00:34:07,460
I need to focus on studying

800
00:34:07,460 --> 00:34:09,100
the litchi transport experiment.

801
00:34:09,700 --> 00:34:10,820
I really can't do it.

802
00:34:11,180 --> 00:34:12,180
I just can't.

803
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:13,260
Can't help.

804
00:34:13,540 --> 00:34:14,380
Can't help.

805
00:34:27,460 --> 00:34:28,866
Chief Scribe Zhao, you're here.

806
00:34:28,866 --> 00:34:29,355
Come in.

807
00:34:29,355 --> 00:34:29,860
Let me carry.

808
00:34:29,860 --> 00:34:30,700
Thank you.

809
00:34:33,700 --> 00:34:34,620
Where is Envoy Li?

810
00:34:34,900 --> 00:34:35,620
Envoy Li?

811
00:34:35,740 --> 00:34:36,580
Over there.

812
00:34:38,580 --> 00:34:40,488
Envoy... Envoy Li.

813
00:34:43,820 --> 00:34:44,660
Chief Scribe Zhao.

814
00:34:46,133 --> 00:34:47,420
What brings you here?

815
00:34:47,780 --> 00:34:49,140
Envoy Li, serving His Majesty,

816
00:34:49,140 --> 00:34:50,540
you really are hands-on.

817
00:34:53,180 --> 00:34:54,660
My wife made some chicken soup.

818
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:56,644
I brought it for you to try.

819
00:34:56,980 --> 00:34:57,820
Much appreciated.

820
00:34:58,620 --> 00:35:00,060
Perfect timing. Let's have a talk.

821
00:35:00,220 --> 00:35:01,060
Good.

822
00:35:01,780 --> 00:35:02,620
Alright, here.

823
00:35:04,780 --> 00:35:05,660
It's not easy at all.

824
00:35:06,460 --> 00:35:08,260
Your wife is quite the cook.

825
00:35:08,580 --> 00:35:09,940
I could smell it through the lid.

826
00:35:09,940 --> 00:35:10,780
Really?

827
00:35:12,100 --> 00:35:13,100
So, are you used

828
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:13,940
to Lingnan cuisine?

829
00:35:14,460 --> 00:35:15,620
To be honest, not really.

830
00:35:16,100 --> 00:35:17,260
Not really.

831
00:35:18,100 --> 00:35:18,940
Understandable.

832
00:35:21,020 --> 00:35:22,060
Envoy Li,

833
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:23,860
you're far from home,

834
00:35:24,060 --> 00:35:25,800
living alone at the post station.

835
00:35:26,380 --> 00:35:28,060
You must miss home terribly.

836
00:35:29,220 --> 00:35:30,180
It can't be easy.

837
00:35:31,140 --> 00:35:32,460
But didn't you already

838
00:35:32,660 --> 00:35:34,340
set off to return to Chang'an?

839
00:35:34,780 --> 00:35:35,780
Why come back again?

840
00:35:37,380 --> 00:35:38,220
All of a sudden,

841
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:40,200
I saw a glimmer of hope.

842
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:42,260
And I wanted to stay

843
00:35:42,900 --> 00:35:43,580
and study

844
00:35:43,580 --> 00:35:44,780
the litchi transport method.

845
00:35:45,755 --> 00:35:47,644
Chief Scribe Zhao,
if you hadn't come today,

846
00:35:47,644 --> 00:35:48,990
I was just about to pay you a visit.

847
00:35:49,800 --> 00:35:51,000
Then my timing was perfect.

848
00:35:52,020 --> 00:35:52,740
What is it?

849
00:35:52,860 --> 00:35:53,911
Feel free to speak openly.

850
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:56,740
Chief Scribe Zhao,

851
00:35:57,500 --> 00:35:58,660
in Lingnan...

852
00:35:59,800 --> 00:36:00,940
Do you have ice?

853
00:36:01,800 --> 00:36:03,377
Soldiers?
[*Both 'soldiers' and 'ice' are pronounced 'bing']

854
00:36:04,860 --> 00:36:06,540
Of course Lingnan has soldiers.

855
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:09,940
May I ask, Envoy Li,

856
00:36:10,333 --> 00:36:12,111
what do you need soldiers for?

857
00:36:12,222 --> 00:36:13,500
To transport litchis,

858
00:36:13,500 --> 00:36:14,500
I need ice.

859
00:36:17,660 --> 00:36:18,500
Ah, I see.

860
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:20,533
Then how many soldiers do you need?

861
00:36:20,780 --> 00:36:22,060
For the trial phase,

862
00:36:22,060 --> 00:36:22,900
not too much.

863
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:24,355
But once we start actual transport,

864
00:36:24,460 --> 00:36:25,460
the more, the better.

865
00:36:28,500 --> 00:36:29,340
I see.

866
00:36:31,180 --> 00:36:33,733
So are you
borrowing the soldiers, Envoy Li?

867
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:36,900
Well...

868
00:36:36,911 --> 00:36:38,340
I'm acting on behalf of His Majesty.

869
00:36:38,340 --> 00:36:39,770
Shouldn't count as borrowing, right?

870
00:36:40,820 --> 00:36:42,200
It should be a requisition.

871
00:36:42,380 --> 00:36:43,780
It should be handed over to me.

872
00:36:46,740 --> 00:36:47,540
Envoy Li,

873
00:36:47,540 --> 00:36:49,355
as expected from someone from Chang'an,

874
00:36:49,500 --> 00:36:50,620
you've seen the world.

875
00:36:52,660 --> 00:36:53,500
No rush.

876
00:36:54,180 --> 00:36:56,260
I'll report this to Inspector He first.

877
00:36:57,511 --> 00:36:58,866
- Thank you.
- I won't keep you.

878
00:36:58,860 --> 00:36:59,888
Much appreciated.

879
00:37:00,100 --> 00:37:00,940
Farewell.

880
00:37:12,330 --> 00:37:14,177
What's wrong
with these Lingnan people...

881
00:37:16,500 --> 00:37:17,580
I said long ago,

882
00:37:17,644 --> 00:37:18,820
this guy should've just been

883
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:19,980
cut down in one stroke.

884
00:37:20,044 --> 00:37:21,688
Keeping him around
is asking for trouble.

885
00:37:21,822 --> 00:37:22,900
And look what happened.

886
00:37:23,020 --> 00:37:23,980
My military tally

887
00:37:23,980 --> 00:37:25,088
hasn't even arrived yet,

888
00:37:25,220 --> 00:37:26,600
and he's already caught the scent,

889
00:37:26,666 --> 00:37:27,844
taking a bite first.

890
00:37:28,860 --> 00:37:29,700
Inspector He.

891
00:37:31,220 --> 00:37:34,111
He invoked
His Majesty's name to request soldiers.

892
00:37:34,140 --> 00:37:35,460
We can't refuse him.

893
00:37:36,177 --> 00:37:37,260
Here to visit you again.

894
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:41,100
This is...

895
00:37:41,940 --> 00:37:44,444
Didn't you say last time
you weren't used to Lingnan food?

896
00:37:44,620 --> 00:37:45,980
This time my wife

897
00:37:45,980 --> 00:37:48,977
specially made
a pot of lamb soup for you.

898
00:37:49,540 --> 00:37:51,320
Such skill.
I can smell it through the lid.

899
00:37:51,780 --> 00:37:53,300
What about the ice?

900
00:37:54,940 --> 00:37:56,820
But Right Chancellor
taught us something.

901
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,380
To get the military tally,

902
00:37:59,822 --> 00:38:01,577
you need to write
a letter of allegiance.

903
00:38:01,900 --> 00:38:02,740
He wants soldiers,

904
00:38:03,020 --> 00:38:05,622
so let's have him submit
a request for troops.

905
00:38:05,660 --> 00:38:06,844
I'll write it right now.

906
00:38:07,500 --> 00:38:08,340
Immediately.

907
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:11,100
Envoy Li,

908
00:38:11,177 --> 00:38:13,200
you really get things done quickly.

909
00:38:14,620 --> 00:38:15,460
This day...

910
00:38:16,500 --> 00:38:17,380
I, Li Shande,

911
00:38:20,460 --> 00:38:22,900
regarding the matter
of transporting litchis,

912
00:38:24,180 --> 00:38:27,180
wish to coordinate
with the Inspector He of Lingnan

913
00:38:28,020 --> 00:38:29,020
to requisition ice.

914
00:38:31,340 --> 00:38:34,100
Humbly ask
that Inspector He grant approval.

915
00:38:36,180 --> 00:38:36,820
Respectfully.

916
00:38:36,940 --> 00:38:37,780
Here.

917
00:38:39,100 --> 00:38:40,420
No... Envoy Li.

918
00:38:41,220 --> 00:38:42,400
Isn't there a mistake?

919
00:38:42,660 --> 00:38:43,500
Soldiers?

920
00:38:43,940 --> 00:38:44,780
I meant ice.

921
00:38:46,340 --> 00:38:48,300
What you want is definitely

922
00:38:48,500 --> 00:38:49,980
ice, the frozen kind?

923
00:38:55,300 --> 00:38:56,420
I misunderstood.

924
00:38:56,700 --> 00:38:57,980
I thought you meant

925
00:38:58,220 --> 00:39:00,780
soldiers to escort the litchis.

926
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:05,340
What a misunderstanding.

927
00:39:06,380 --> 00:39:08,220
No wonder you looked troubled yesterday.

928
00:39:08,266 --> 00:39:09,500
I didn't express myself clearly.

929
00:39:10,666 --> 00:39:13,022
We haven't even solved
how to keep the litchis fresh.

930
00:39:13,060 --> 00:39:15,222
What's the point of talking
about military escorts?

931
00:39:15,580 --> 00:39:16,220
So...

932
00:39:16,340 --> 00:39:17,500
About the ice,

933
00:39:17,577 --> 00:39:19,140
I'll need your help, Chief Scribe Zhao.

934
00:39:19,540 --> 00:39:20,500
Envoy Li,

935
00:39:20,740 --> 00:39:21,900
when it comes to ice,

936
00:39:22,700 --> 00:39:24,940
it's going to be even harder.

937
00:39:25,755 --> 00:39:27,044
You know as well as I do,

938
00:39:27,300 --> 00:39:28,380
Lingnan is hot and humid.

939
00:39:28,620 --> 00:39:29,780
It's nothing like Chang'an.

940
00:39:29,980 --> 00:39:32,733
I've never even seen ice
since I was a child.

941
00:39:32,933 --> 00:39:34,780
You could say it's harder
to find than gold.

942
00:39:35,060 --> 00:39:36,420
Almost impossible.

943
00:39:38,580 --> 00:39:40,780
So then wasn't my writing
all for nothing?

944
00:39:42,860 --> 00:39:44,140
I'll just take it back.

945
00:39:47,380 --> 00:39:49,380
Let's think of a solution together.

946
00:39:50,620 --> 00:39:51,460
Farewell.

947
00:39:51,900 --> 00:39:52,740
Much obliged.

948
00:39:58,140 --> 00:40:00,180
My wife specifically told me

949
00:40:00,180 --> 00:40:01,444
to bring the clay pot back.

950
00:40:11,260 --> 00:40:12,460
So based on what you're saying,

951
00:40:13,020 --> 00:40:14,380
you've come across another master.

952
00:40:14,740 --> 00:40:15,700
And a deep one at that.

953
00:40:16,020 --> 00:40:16,860
Exactly.

954
00:40:17,180 --> 00:40:18,340
With just a few words,

955
00:40:18,780 --> 00:40:20,020
he flipped truth and lies.

956
00:40:20,780 --> 00:40:21,940
When I dealt with him,

957
00:40:22,340 --> 00:40:23,060
of course,

958
00:40:23,180 --> 00:40:24,340
we were equally matched.

959
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:26,977
But every move was risky.

960
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:28,220
I had to stay sharp,

961
00:40:28,500 --> 00:40:29,780
respond on the spot,

962
00:40:30,380 --> 00:40:31,260
go with the flow,

963
00:40:31,740 --> 00:40:33,644
and speak without giving anything away.

964
00:40:34,100 --> 00:40:35,580
Sounds like you're quite pleased,

965
00:40:36,220 --> 00:40:38,140
thinking you and Li Shande are equals.

966
00:40:38,140 --> 00:40:38,620
Yes.

967
00:40:38,740 --> 00:40:39,340
Nonsense.

968
00:40:39,460 --> 00:40:40,380
The way I see it,

969
00:40:40,780 --> 00:40:41,540
this time around,

970
00:40:41,660 --> 00:40:43,060
he had you utterly beat.

971
00:40:43,060 --> 00:40:43,700
He didn't.

972
00:40:43,820 --> 00:40:44,660
Oh, please.

973
00:40:45,220 --> 00:40:46,660
Didn't Kongming once say,

974
00:40:46,688 --> 00:40:47,780
if the enemy doesn't move,

975
00:40:48,300 --> 00:40:49,140
I won't move either.

976
00:40:49,740 --> 00:40:50,580
If the enemy...

977
00:40:52,940 --> 00:40:53,580
If...

978
00:40:53,580 --> 00:40:54,977
The enemy moves, and I strike first.

979
00:40:55,020 --> 00:40:55,860
Exactly.

980
00:40:56,340 --> 00:40:58,380
He merely said the word "ice",

981
00:40:58,380 --> 00:40:59,780
and look how flustered you got.

982
00:41:00,220 --> 00:41:01,740
You rushed off to dig for answers.

983
00:41:01,777 --> 00:41:02,380
And the result?

984
00:41:02,380 --> 00:41:03,980
He found out everything about us.

985
00:41:04,660 --> 00:41:05,900
Now what am I supposed to do?

986
00:41:07,060 --> 00:41:07,900
Do what?

987
00:41:09,540 --> 00:41:10,380
Inspector He,

988
00:41:10,980 --> 00:41:12,100
try this lamb soup first.

989
00:41:13,260 --> 00:41:14,820
Yes, it must be eaten.

990
00:41:16,580 --> 00:41:17,820
I heard the people of Chang'an

991
00:41:17,822 --> 00:41:18,860
love this kind of soup.

992
00:41:18,860 --> 00:41:19,700
Right?

993
00:41:19,940 --> 00:41:20,780
Very nourishing.

994
00:41:22,860 --> 00:41:23,460
Excellent.

995
00:41:34,940 --> 00:41:35,780
Master Konglang.

996
00:41:36,644 --> 00:41:38,420
How's the situation with the camel?

997
00:41:39,460 --> 00:41:40,300
We've

998
00:41:40,488 --> 00:41:42,511
run into a tough one this time.

999
00:41:42,555 --> 00:41:43,780
Can't get a bite out of it.

1000
00:42:05,700 --> 00:42:06,911
We can't afford to fail.

1001
00:42:07,580 --> 00:42:08,377
Yes.

1002
00:42:32,020 --> 00:42:34,860
=The Litchi Road=

1003
00:42:35,155 --> 00:42:36,220
So this deadly matter...

1004
00:42:37,420 --> 00:42:38,260
Whose life is it?

1005
00:42:38,460 --> 00:42:39,300
Yours.

1006
00:42:39,660 --> 00:42:40,500
It can't be saved.

1007
00:42:41,540 --> 00:42:42,620
You jest.

1008
00:42:43,020 --> 00:42:43,860
How could that be?

1009
00:42:45,540 --> 00:42:46,660
How could it be so sudden?

1010
00:42:47,140 --> 00:42:49,155
I've got the kind of luck
that pulls me through

1011
00:42:49,150 --> 00:42:50,933
when things get hopeless.

1012
00:42:51,022 --> 00:42:51,780
I won't die.

1013
00:42:52,540 --> 00:42:53,500
I'll just pass

1014
00:42:53,740 --> 00:42:54,460
this bad luck

1015
00:42:54,580 --> 00:42:55,700
onto someone else.

1016
00:42:55,900 --> 00:42:56,940
Then that person

1017
00:42:57,260 --> 00:42:58,020
is simply unlucky,

1018
00:42:58,140 --> 00:42:59,220
a cursed wretch,

1019
00:42:59,340 --> 00:43:00,511
and a doomed soul.

1020
00:43:01,060 --> 00:43:01,940
And if I give up?

1021
00:43:02,820 --> 00:43:03,660
Master Konglang

1022
00:43:04,100 --> 00:43:05,460
will never let you

1023
00:43:05,980 --> 00:43:06,940
leave Lingnan alive.

1024
00:43:07,780 --> 00:43:08,300
Qilang.

1025
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,700
Although I cling to a branch
in Lingnan

1026
00:43:23,700 --> 00:43:25,530
I'm popular

1027
00:43:26,050 --> 00:43:28,560
My immortal aura drifted to Chang'an

1028
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:29,970
Driving people mad

1029
00:43:30,750 --> 00:43:33,010
Who wore out their shoes for me

1030
00:43:33,010 --> 00:43:35,190
Running around all day without rest

1031
00:43:35,630 --> 00:43:37,800
Just to earn a sweet fruit to eat?

1032
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:39,580
Everyone
wants a taste of something new

1033
00:43:40,350 --> 00:43:42,540
I stumble through mountains, rivers,
lakes, and seas

1034
00:43:42,540 --> 00:43:44,590
In my dreams

1035
00:43:45,070 --> 00:43:47,230
Endless deceit

1036
00:43:47,230 --> 00:43:48,930
Absurd negotiation

1037
00:43:49,870 --> 00:43:51,940
I also want to see
red tiles and golden bricks

1038
00:43:51,940 --> 00:43:54,060
A prosperous world

1039
00:43:54,600 --> 00:43:55,710
But all I see

1040
00:43:55,710 --> 00:43:58,730
Is a man crying all night

1041
00:43:59,100 --> 00:44:01,600
A little bit every day

1042
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:04,110
A little bit crazier

1043
00:44:04,110 --> 00:44:07,410
I was once carefree in Lingnan

1044
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:12,330
Only sharing the moonlight
with heaven and earth

1045
00:44:12,770 --> 00:44:17,280
I'm popular but with nowhere to rest

1046
00:44:17,530 --> 00:44:21,710
I saw the greed of the world

1047
